Malaba boda boda operators have said the contractor given the job to tarmac the Busia-Malaba road is asleep on the job. The boda boda operators said nothing much has been done on the road. In December 2016, President Uhuru Kenyatta launched construction work on the road linking the two border towns of Busia-Malaba. A total of Sh1 billion was injected to the project. The road was expected to open up the region, besides linking residents to Uganda. It is expected to ease movement of goods and services.   The boda boda operators said the contractor should the example of another Chinese contractor who is constructing the Malaba-Lwakhakha road. Operator John Chemo said the Chinese contractor is doing a commendable job on the 15km stretch of road.      